l issue with dynamic proxy metadata for `jline.console.completer.Completer`, which I need to watch for. Plus, testing with a v1 isolated ClassLoader might throw a `ClassNotFoundException`. To improve this, I could try catching exceptions for native calls without skipping but still need to follow the rules. Maybe removing the v1 test could help avoid dynamic class loading but complicates hitting those lines.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring testing options**\\n\\nI’m considering if there’s a way to create an active report with one attempt while ensuring V2 is covered without native risks. The user wants improvement, so I’m wondering if we could handle V1 without dynamic class loading to avoid native issues, perhaps by using a separate process? If a JUnit test launches a Java subprocess with a filtered classpath, that could work. But under Native, I’m not sure launching Java will be possible in CI. It might allow for unsupported errors due to dynamic classloading.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TV92Qlw5SuNVtpKHjYyn8Bwd|fc_0feb8217bb60951e0169fa51ef556c819db54e6a523fc32815", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/jline/ConsoleReader.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    public void addCompletor(Completor completor) {\n        COMPLETIONS.clear();\n        completor.complete(\"hel\", 3, COMPLETIONS);\n    }\n", "newText": "    public void addCompletor(Completor completor) {\n        COMPLETIONS.clear();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 440, "output": 1044, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35276, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778012640282, "responseId": "resp_0feb8217bb60951e0169fa51e10de0819dabdd1e3cdae9cfb4"}}
